bio:
Photo/image retouching/editing is my passion as well as photography. I strive to deliver the highest quality within the shortest time and aim to constantly grow through self-developing in this field. 

I pay lots of attention to details, deliver on time, and have a positive and optimistic attitude and passion for what I do bring out the best in photos, with a very natural, clean and realistic look.

My major projects are focused on editing studio, portrait, beauty, fashion, corporate and lifestyle photography. I prefer using only non-destructive methods while working on the skin, no blurring, mostly dodging&burning on the pore level (same technique as chosen by Annie Leibovitz for her portraits).

My Photoshop skills include (but are not limited to):
✓ general;
✓ blemish removal;
✓ dodge & burn;
✓ reshape and retouch the body;
✓ enhance the eye colour;
✓ refine lips & mouth;
✓ transform shape with liquify;
✓ face-aware liquify;
✓ frequency separation;
✓ colour-tone portraits;
✓ advanced sharpening for faces;
✓ match skin tones;
✓ luminosity painting;
✓ combine multiple exposures to increase dynamic range (HDR);
✓ luminosity masks;
✓ swap heads from different photos;
✓ recover highlights and shadows;
✓ background retouch & clean-up.

Soft/hardware used:
✓ latest version of Photoshop on MacBook Pro;
✓ Wacom Intuos Pro graphic tablet;
✓  AI tools.

